h3. Summary

The {{mailto:}} markup doesn't render the email link when it has a leading underscore, eg. {{_johndoe@company.com}}

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Go to a page.
# Add the following markup:
{code}
[mailto:_johndoe@company.com]
{code}

h3. Expected Results
A link with the email address will be created. You also will be able to click on this link.

h3. Actual Results

The link is not created. It turns to pure text.

Output on the page:
{code}
_johndoe@company.com (mailto:_johndoe@company.com)
{code} 

h3. Notes
Happening in all browsers.

h3. Workaround
{panel}
# Use the following markup:
{noformat}
[mailto://_johdoe@company.com]
{noformat}
# Edit the text link and remove the "//".
{panel}
It's not feasible to perform the workaround because the email link will continue to be {{//_johndoe@company.com}}.

