h5.Steps to Reproduce
# On a space that's using the documentation theme, click "Configure Theme"
# Untick "Page Tree"
# For the "Navigation" text box, add the following Wiki Markup:
{code}
{pagetree:startDepth=1|expandCollapseAll=true|searchBox=true}
{code}

h5.Expected Results:
The Page Tree Macro displays correctly

h5.Actual Results:
The "Expand" label has a negative margin, and truncates to the left of the screen.

h5.Workaround:
Add the following CSS to your instance (if you have more than one space with this problem, apply the CSS at the site level):

{code}
#splitter-sidebar .plugin_pagetree_expandcollapse { text-indent: 20px }
{code}

h5.Note about the Documentation theme
The Documentation Theme is deprecated in Confluence 5.9, and will be removed for Confluence Server in version 6.0. This information is provided as a workaround only.

